ays to Track Scholarship Results in Turkiye","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarship-results-follow-up/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarship-results-follow-up/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/the-easiest-ways-to-track-scholarship-results-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarship-results-follow-up/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading">When are scholarship results announced?</h2>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How is the scholarship application calendar in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each scholarship institution has its own application and result announcement calendar. State scholarships such as KYK usually receive applications in <strong>October-November</strong> and announce the results in December. Private foundations or intra-university scholarships may make announcements from time to time. It is therefore critical to check official websites regularly.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For example, for <strong>TEV</strong> or <strong>Directorate General of Foundations</strong> scholarships, the &#8220;scholarship results&#8221; are usually announced on their platforms. If you miss the process, you will have to wait for the next semester. And in Turkey, missing a scholarship can sometimes be a bigger problem than school.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="where-to-find-out-when-the-results-are-announced">Where to find out when the results are announced?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The institution&#8217;s announcement page should be your primary source. However, most students are content with the information shared on social media and may miss the &#8220;scholarship results&#8221; even if they have been announced. The safest method: checking e-Government and the relevant scholarship pages directly.</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you received a scholarship without a dormitory, be sure to check out our article on <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/private-state-dormitories/" data-type="post" data-id="4655">The Relationship between Dormitory Accommodation and Residence Permit in Turkey</a>. Because the dormitory and residence status of scholarship students are directly linked to each other.</p>
</blockquote>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-track-foundation-and-private-institution-scholarships">How to Track Foundation and Private Institution Scholarships</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How are TEV, VGM and other foundation scholarships announced?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many sources outside of state institutions, but most students bypass them. <strong>TEV (Turkish Education Foundation)</strong>, <strong>Directorate General of Foundations (DGF)</strong> and even some municipalities award scholarships once or twice a year. The results of these scholarships are usually announced on their website or through the portal where you apply.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">TEV, for example, uses the &#8220;Obigenç&#8221; platform. When TEV scholarship results are announced, you can log in to your user account through this application and see the results. The same goes for VGM; the institution announces the results on the &#8220;announcements&#8221; tab on its website. Sometimes they may also require a document completion process, so it&#8217;s worth keeping an eye on them frequently.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-use-platforms-like-obigenc">How to use platforms like Obigenc?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Obigenç is a practical system where you can track both your scholarship application and the evaluation process. After logging in, you can see the results such as &#8220;under evaluation&#8221;, &#8220;winner&#8221;, &#8220;reserve&#8221; in the &#8220;application status&#8221; tab. TEV scholarship results are usually announced in late October or early November. If you miss this deadline, your application may be wasted.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">And yes, if you&#8217;ve come this far, now you know: &#8220;scholarship results&#8221; is not only about applying, but also about checking at the right time.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="e-devletinden-burs-ve-kredi-sorgulama">Scholarship and Loan Inquiry from e-Government</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-view-kyk-scholarship-and-student-loans">How to view KYK scholarship and student loans?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The clearest and most reliable source of information for scholarships and student loans provided by KYK is the <strong>e-Devlet</strong> system. When the &#8220;scholarship results&#8221; are announced, you can find out your status in seconds through the system.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All you have to do: Go to <a href="https://www.turkiye.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Learning / Contribution Loan and Scholarship Inquiry</em></a> and log in with your Turkish ID number. If you do not have Turkish citizenship, you should get information from your university or scholarship provider.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="payment-inquiry-via-ptt">Payment Inquiry via PTT</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="learn-whether-there-is-a-scholarship-with-live-support">Learn whether there is a scholarship with live support</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">OK, let&#8217;s say the &#8220;scholarship results&#8221; have been announced, but no money has been deposited into your account yet. Don&#8217;t panic. For this, you can check whether your payment has been processed via <strong>PTT</strong>. You go to the <strong>live support</strong> section on <a href="https://www.ptt.gov.tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PTT&#8217;s official site</a> and enter your information. Current payment status is given from there.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-the-ptt-system-suitable-for-international-students">Is the PTT system suitable for international students?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">PTT usually provides fast service to Turkish citizens, but foreign students can also make inquiries with their foreign ID number. Sometimes there can be a delay in the system, so it makes sense to check again 1-2 days later, not on the day the results are announced. Especially the first scholarship payment is sometimes late.</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you received a scholarship through the Erasmus program, our article <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Visa Procedures for Erasmus and Exchange Students in Turkey</a> is of interest to you. Because the payment and registration processes of these students work a little differently.</p>
</blockquote>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequent-mistakes-and-tips-to-avoid-missing-out">Frequent Mistakes and Tips to Avoid Missing Out</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="can-email-and-sms-notifications-be-trusted">Can email and SMS notifications be trusted?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Unfortunately, no. Although most institutions say they send notifications, these messages sometimes end up in the spam box and sometimes never arrive. So it is a serious risk to rely only on e-mail when the &#8220;scholarship results&#8221; are announced.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Email and SMS are just an additional reminder, not an official source. Small foundations or universities, especially in Turkey, only announce results on their website. To stay up to date, save the calendar on your phone and go directly to the site on results days.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-some-students-cant-see-the-results">Why some students can&#8217;t see the results?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are several reasons for this: Wrong application number, missing documents, technical errors in the system or simply logging in late. The KYK system can be particularly busy, which can cause the &#8220;scholarship results&#8221; screen not to open. My advice: be patient, try again several times during the day.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="get-notified-about-scholarships-in-turkey-on-time">Get Notified About Scholarships in Turkey on Time</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="road-to-study-makes-the-process-easier">Road to Study makes the process easier</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Now you know that the scholarship application process requires as much strategy as the scholarship results process. A common mistake of international students studying in Turkey is to focus only on the application and miss the results. That&#8217;s why you need the right source.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="enter-the-next-application-period-prepared">Enter the next application period prepared!</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you don&#8217;t want to be caught unprepared, now is the time to take steps. Tracking <strong>scholarship results</strong> is as serious as the applications. Take action today, make your plan, prepare your documents and work with the right resources. It is up to you not to miss out on scholarship opportunities in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to win a turkey scholarship?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Winning a scholarship to study in Turkey requires a strong academic record, well-written motivation letter, and participation in extracurricular activities. You should also highlight your unique skills and future plans.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much GPA is required for a scholarship in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Generally, a GPA of at least 70% for undergraduate programs, 75% for master&#8217;s programs, and 80% for PhD programs is required. However, higher GPAs increase your chances significantly.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Is Türkiye bursu scholarship competitive?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, the Türkiye Bursları scholarship is highly competitive. It receives a massive number of applications from all over the world, so a strong application with excellent academic results and a compelling motivation letter is essential to stand out.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the 100% scholarship in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A 100% scholarship in Turkey typically covers tuition fees fully. Some comprehensive scholarships, like the Türkiye Bursları, also include a monthly stipend, accommodation, health insurance, and round-trip airfare, making them a full scholarship.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-11T09:53:16Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T19:22:09Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/the-easiest-ways-to-track-scholarship-results-in-turkey.webp","alt":"A man sitting at a table, calculating and checking scholarship results","title":"the-easiest-ways-to-track-scholarship-results-in-turkey"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'turkey-scholarship-results-follow-up';
