<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-crowdfunding-what-is-the-legal-situation-in-turkey">What is Crowdfunding? What is the Legal Situation in Turkey?</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="definition-and-basic-types-of-crowdfunding">Definition and Basic Types of Crowdfunding</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Crowdfunding</strong> is a way of achieving big goals by collecting small donations from a large audience. It is used in many areas such as education, arts, technology, but lately it has been making a real difference, especially for individual students. There are four main types: donation-based, reward-based, debt-based and investment-based. The most commonly used donation-based <strong>crowdfunding</strong> for education works through unconditional support.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-legal-framework-of-crowdfunding-in-turkey">The Legal Framework of Crowdfunding in Turkey</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Crowdfunding </strong>in Turkey was put on an official footing with a legal regulation in 2017. The Capital Markets Board (CMB) assumed the supervisory authority in this field with the communiqué published in 2019. This paved the way for start-ups to meet their capital needs by collecting investments from the public. It is aimed to support companies with innovative business models, especially those focused on technology and production.</p>



