d to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/ozyegin-universitesi-scholarship-tours.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/ozyegin-universitesi-scholarship-tours.webp","width":"1024","height":"604","caption":"Types of scholarships offered at Özyeğin University","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ozyegin-university-scholarship/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ozyegin-university-scholarship/","name":"Ozyegin University Scholarship Opportunities: Application Guide","datePublished":"2025-07-21T16:14:15+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:52:47+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/ozyegin-universitesi-scholarship-tours.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Ozyegin University Scholarship Opportunities: Application Guide","keywords":"Özyeğin University Scholarship","datePublished":"2025-07-21T16:14:15+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:52:47+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Özyeğin University scholarship opportunities. Application process, fees and merit scholarships are waiting for you! Apply now, don&#039;t miss the opportunity.","name":"Ozyegin University Scholarship Opportunities: Application Guide","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ozyegin-university-scholarship/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ozyegin-university-scholarship/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/ozyegin-universitesi-scholarship-tours.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/ozyegin-university-scholarship/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">What are the types of scholarships at Ozyegin University?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University takes a very generous approach to scholarship opportunities. The university has created an inclusive system by awarding scholarships not only for academic achievement, but also for sports skills and social needs. Although it may seem challenging to get a scholarship, especially for foreign students, many people can continue their education with financial support thanks to the <strong>özyeğin university scholarship</strong> program.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="intrance-scholarships-for-international-students">Intrance Scholarships for International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each year, <strong>undergraduate entrance scholarships</strong> for international students are awarded between 25% and 100% depending on the academic performance presented at the time of application. The university evaluates the student overall, taking into account grades, diploma score, letters of reference and motivational letter. So it&#8217;s not just high grades, but also a good application package.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="academic-success-scholarships">Academic Success Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <strong>academic merit scholarships</strong> provided for current students are usually based on the year-end grade point average. </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In a nutshell, merit scholarships are based on systemic success, not on direct application. At the end of the academic year, a ranking is made for the 1st, 2nd and 3rd year quotas of each faculty. Students with the highest GPA are eligible for this scholarship if they meet the minimum credit and GPA requirements. This scholarship provides <strong>25% tuition fee waiver</strong> and is awarded only for the major of enrollment.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sports-scholarships-for-successful-students-ozyegin-university-sports-scholarship">Sports Scholarships for Successful Students: Özyeğin University Sports Scholarship</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>The <em>Sports Scholarship</em>, one of the scholarship options at Ozyegin University, rewards not only academic but also sporting achievements. If you are a professional or licensed athlete and are ready to represent the university, this scholarship could be for you.</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Sports scholarships are re-evaluated at the beginning of each academic year. The <strong>Sports Center Directorate</strong> determines which branches will be supported, the application conditions and the continuation conditions of the scholarship. In general, students who are active in team or individual sports branches such as swimming, basketball, volleyball and athletics can apply.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Earning this scholarship depends not only on your talent but also on your academic success. Özyeğin aims to support athletes who are both intelligent and disciplined.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to get more details, you can check out the <a href="https://www.ozyegin.edu.tr/en/sport-center/athletic-scholarships" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official scholarship information</a> directly from the university.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="ozyegin-university-scholarship-opportunities-and-merit-scholarship">Özyegin University Scholarship Opportunities and Merit Scholarship</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For many international students, getting a scholarship for success at university can almost seem like a &#8220;dream&#8221;. But the <strong>özyeğin University scholarship</strong> system is one of the examples that turns this dream into reality. In addition to the entrance scholarship you receive in the first year, you can also earn new scholarships during your studies based on your academic success. This provides both financial comfort and a serious motivation to work harder.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-is-awarded-the-success-scholarship">Who is awarded the Success Scholarship?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These scholarships are available for students studying in undergraduate programs without scholarships or with partial scholarships. In particular, students who meet the following conditions are automatically evaluated every year <strong>at the end of the spring semester</strong>:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Have not graduated by the end of the spring semester</li>



<li>Be a registered student at OzU for at least two semesters</li>



<li>Have a GPA of at least 3.00</li>



<li>To have completed at least 24 ECTS courses in both fall and spring semesters</li>



<li>No disciplinary penalties</li>



<li>To have completed the following credit load according to the number of semesters studied:</li>
</ul>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Semester of Study</th>
<th>Minimum Required Credits</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>2 Semester</td>
<td>54 ECTS</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>3 Semester</td>
<td>84 ECTS</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>4 Term</td>
<td>114 ECTS</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>5 Term</td>
<td>144 ECTS</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>6 Term</td>
<td>174 ECTS</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>7 Term</td>
<td>204 ECTS</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This scholarship is allocated to <strong>3 students each</strong> in the 1st, 2nd and 3rd year quotas for each faculty and college. So in total, we can say that there are 9 quotas per department per year.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-is-ranking-and-evaluation-done">How is Ranking and Evaluation Done?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Ozyeğin University scholarship</strong> evaluation is based entirely on academic data. At the end of the spring semester, students are ranked according to their GPA. If the average is equal, the ranking continues according to the following criteria:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Total number of loans</li>



<li>GPA for that year</li>



<li>Amount of completed loans for the year</li>



<li>No F, D or C- grades in the courses taken</li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The winning students are determined by the Student Services Directorate and the scholarships are finalized with the approval of the rectorate. So you don&#8217;t need to apply for this scholarship <strong>also</strong>; the system recognizes you if you deserve it.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Thanks to this system, a student who starts with a low scholarship in the first year can have the chance to get more scholarships by proving himself in the following years.</p>


