<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Fees are determined by the Board of Trustees at the beginning of each academic year. Students can make their payments in Turkish Lira instead of foreign currency, based on the <strong>Central Bank of the Republic of Turkey&#8217;s foreign exchange buying rate</strong>. You can find more information on <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ozyegin-universitesi-egitim-ucretleri/" data-type="post" data-id="3013">Özyeğin University Tuition Fees and Payment Options</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-and-support-programs">Scholarship and Support Programs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All applicants who apply to OzU are <strong>automatically considered for scholarships.</strong> No separate application is required. The scholarship rates are: 25%, 30%, 35%, 40%, 45% and 50%.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships are awarded based on <strong>academic achievement</strong>, outstanding extracurricular activities and motivational letters. In addition, program availability and comparison with other applicants are taken into consideration. All applicants are automatically considered for a scholarship.</p>



