<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="general-information-about-faculty-of-engineering">General Information About Faculty of Engineering</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University&#8217;s Faculty of Engineering has been offering students an education at global standards since 2009. The programs, which were structured by examining engineering faculties both in Turkey and around the world during the establishment phase, today have international accreditations.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Faculty data as of 2023:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>2186 undergraduate students</li>



<li>435 graduate students</li>



<li>141 doctoral students</li>



<li>75 faculty members</li>



<li>47 research laboratories</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The vision of the faculty is to be among the world&#8217;s leading engineering faculties in education and research. Its mission is to train engineers who benefit humanity through the production of technological knowledge.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="engineering-departments-and-education-infrastructure">Engineering Departments and Education Infrastructure</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="offered-engineering-programs">Offered Engineering Programs</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Section</th>
<th>2025-2026 Fee (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Artificial Intelligence and Data Engineering</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Computer Engineering</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Electrical Engineering</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Industrial Engineering</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Mechanical Engineering</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Civil Engineering</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="episode-focused-short-introductions">Episode Focused Short Introductions</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Computer Engineering:</strong> Aiming to transform young people from technology users to creators, the program provides students with the knowledge base needed to create complex systems such as mobile phones.</li>



<li><strong>Electrical-Electronics Engineering:</strong> Aims to train researcher and entrepreneurial engineers with projects integrated with industry and advanced electronics applications.</li>



<li><strong>Industrial Engineering:</strong> Trains solution-oriented engineers who have a good command of technology based on process and system efficiency.</li>



<li><strong>Mechanical Engineering:</strong> Trains scientifically and technically equipped engineers who can take an active role in the design and production of new technologies.</li>



<li><strong>Civil Engineering:</strong> Structured to train research-oriented and versatile engineers who are capable of working in different geographies.</li>



<li><strong>Artificial Intelligence and Data Engineering:</strong> Aims to train engineers who will build the artificial intelligence systems of the future with world-class education.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All engineering programs are <strong>MÜDEK accredited</strong> and the program duration is 4 years.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="educational-language-and-curriculum-structure">Educational Language and Curriculum Structure</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All engineering programs are taught <strong>100% in English</strong>. The curriculum is structured in such a way as to offer theory and practice together. Compulsory summer internships, graduation projects and elective course pools ensure that students are trained as industry-ready graduates.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="modern-laboratories-and-applied-education">Modern Laboratories and Applied Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Engineering students gain hands-on experience in more than 47 laboratories at the university. The faculty has MÜDEK accreditation and students&#8217; projects take part in international competitions.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="fees-scholarships-and-financial-facilities">Fees, Scholarships and Financial Facilities</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="updated-tuition-fees-ydo-2024-2025">Updated Tuition Fees (YDO 2024-2025)</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Fee Item</th>
<th>Amount (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>License Tuition</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Preparatory Program Fee</td>
<td>$22,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Summer School (Per Credit)</td>
<td>1/60 of the annual fee</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Housing, Food, Insurance</td>
<td>Excluded</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Fees are determined by the Board of Trustees at the beginning of each academic year. Students can make their payments in Turkish Lira instead of foreign currency, based on the <strong>Central Bank of the Republic of Turkey&#8217;s foreign exchange buying rate</strong>. You can find more information on <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ozyegin-universitesi-egitim-ucretleri/" data-type="post" data-id="3013">Özyeğin University Tuition Fees and Payment Options</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-and-support-programs">Scholarship and Support Programs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All applicants who apply to OzU are <strong>automatically considered for scholarships.</strong> No separate application is required. The scholarship rates are: 25%, 30%, 35%, 40%, 45% and 50%.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships are awarded based on <strong>academic achievement</strong>, outstanding extracurricular activities and motivational letters. In addition, program availability and comparison with other applicants are taken into consideration. All applicants are automatically considered for a scholarship.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="example-2025-2026-payment-plans">Example 2025-2026 Payment Plans</h4>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
