<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="transportation-maps-and-navigation-life-between-campuses">Transportation, Maps and Navigation: Life Between Campuses</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Ozyeğin campuses</strong> are strategically located to facilitate student life in a big city like Istanbul. Whether it is <strong>özyeğin University Çeköy</strong> or <strong>özyeğin University Altunizade Campus</strong>, both campuses are easily accessible by public transportation, private car or university shuttles.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I had to change five different buses to get to campus in the first week. Then student affairs sent me a link to a map and the shuttle times, and my life was saved. Here are the details of that system:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-transportation-between-cekmekoy-and-altunizade-easy">Is Transportation Between Çekmeköy and Altunizade Easy?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The average distance between the two campuses is 25 kilometers. Transportation time varies between 40 and 60 minutes depending on traffic conditions. It is possible to reach by the following methods:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Metro:</strong> Direct transportation between Üsküdar and Çekmeköy with M5 line.</li>



<li><strong>Bus &amp; Minibus:</strong> There are IETT lines and minibus routes passing near the campus. For detailed route information, <a>IETT Official Website</a> can be used.</li>



<li><strong>University Shuttles:</strong> Özyeğin University offers free shuttle service at certain hours.</li>
