<p class="wp-block-paragraph">What does this mean? The department is flexible not only academically but also in terms of financial access. Successful students in the upper bracket are supported with full scholarships, while students with more average scores are offered 50% scholarships or paid options.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> Özyeğin University has also been steadily rising in academic ranking platforms such as <a href="https://newtr.urapcenter.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">URAP</a> and YÖK Atlas. Metrics such as the number of scientific publications, international collaborations, entrepreneurship support and graduate employment directly affect this success.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In short: Regardless of your ranking, with the right strategy, you have a good chance of getting into this department.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-does-computer-engineering-education-cost-2025">How Much Does Computer Engineering Education Cost? 2025</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many private universities in Turkey update their tuition fees every year. Özyeğin University has set the <strong>annual tuition fee for the <strong>Faculty of Engineering</strong> at 22,000 USD</strong> as of 2025. This fee is the standard list for non-scholarship (i.e. 0% scholarship) students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Below, you can see the current fee and scholarship status of Özyeğin University Faculty of Engineering for the year 2025 &#8211; 2026 according to the departments:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2025-faculty-of-computer-engineering-fee-table">2025 Faculty of Computer Engineering Fee Table</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Department</th>
<th>Cost of Study (USD/Year)</th>
<th>Language of Study</th>
<th>Scholarship Opportunities</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Computer Engineering</strong></td>
<td>$22,000</td>
<td>English</td>
<td>Full / 50% / Paid</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These fees are annual and do not remain fixed throughout the study period; the university may update them by 10-20% each year. However, the scholarship rate indicated at the time of admission remains fixed for the entire duration of the student&#8217;s studies.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-do-you-pay-with-scholarships">How much do you pay with scholarships?</h4>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Full Scholarship</strong>: $0 (Free)</li>



<li><strong>50% Scholarship</strong>: $11,000</li>



<li><strong>Paid</strong> (without scholarship): $22,000</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These fees include laboratory use, academic advising, library access and some technical materials. Accommodation and meals are charged separately. Average dormitory prices are <strong>3,000-5,000 USD</strong> per year, and living expenses are around <strong>3,000 USD</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When we consider the cost of education and living, we can easily say that it is a much more economical option compared to universities in Europe or America.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="where-do-graduates-work-internship-and-career-opportunities">Where Do Graduates Work? Internship and Career Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Speaking of careers: Özyeğin University has established a strong connection with the business world. Graduates work for major technology companies in Turkey as well as global companies such as Amazon, Google and Microsoft. Especially students with a good project track record and English communication skills start receiving job offers even before they graduate.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="internships-are-not-just-formalities">Internships Are Not Just Formalities</h4>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>most students have direct contact with the industry from the first grade. Thanks to the university&#8217;s Career Center, students can do internships in companies such as Turkcell, Trendyol and Insider. The university also offers summer internships in countries such as Germany, the Netherlands and Poland through Erasmus+ programs.</li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the department, &#8220;graduation projects&#8221; are based entirely on real sectoral problems. Professors usually involve students in their own research topics and these projects can be turned into publications.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are interested in entrepreneurship, OzU-X is for you. They offer support for technology-based business ideas to meet with investors, build teams and even develop prototypes.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="International Student Testimonials - Pakistan" width="720" height="405" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/uMrQJrLf0A0?start=30&#038;feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 23px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 23px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-renewal-conditions-in-turkey-and-things-to-consider">Scholarship Renewal Conditions in Turkey and Things to Consider</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">At the end of the second year, most students who get a scholarship for the first year ask the following question: &#8220;Will my scholarship be cut off?&#8221; Indeed, the scholarship renewal requirements at foundation universities in Turkey can sometimes cause students to lose their scholarships.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the table below, you can see the standard conditions usually required for scholarships to continue in Turkey:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-renewal-requirements-general">🎓 Scholarship Renewal Requirements (General)</h3>


<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Criterion</strong></th>
<th><strong>Explanation</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Academic GPA</td>
<td>Usually a GPA above 2.0 / 4.0 is required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Course Repetition</td>
<td>Scholarship may be terminated if a course is taken more than twice</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Disciplinary Action</td>
<td>Penalties beyond a warning may lead to scholarship cancellation</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Duration of Study</td>
<td>Scholarship ends at the end of the 5th year for a 4-year program</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Attendance and In-Person Participation</td>
<td>Failure to meet attendance requirements may put the scholarship at risk</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These items may vary according to each university. At Özyeğin University, scholarships are usually evaluated based on disciplinary action and minimum GPA. Note that the scholarship is not automatically renewed and the student must check their performance every year.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are interested in this topic, you can also take a look at our guide on how to keep your scholarship: <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-burs-yenileme/" data-type="post" data-id="2906">Scholarship Renewal Requirements and Considerations in Turkey</a></p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="studying-computer-engineering-at-ozyegin">Studying Computer Engineering at Ozyegin</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you have questions like &#8220;Can I apply?&#8221; or &#8220;Will my score be enough?&#8221;, you are not alone. This is exactly how I felt during the first application process. But the secret is to start from the right place.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a> guides you through every step of the application process. You will receive step-by-step support both in preparing documents and using the online application platform. And the consultation is completely free.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Now is the time to act.</strong> The application process is open throughout the year, but quotas are filling up fast. Don&#8217;t postpone your dream; start your computer engineering career at Özyeğin in Istanbul.</p>



