<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Mathematics:</strong> Calculus, Linear Algebra, Differential Equations</li>



<li><strong>Physics:</strong> Electricity and Magnetism, Mechanics</li>



<li><strong>Programming:</strong> Python, C/C++, MATLAB</li>



<li><strong>Mechanics and Thermodynamics</strong></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="field-specialization-courses">Field Specialization Courses</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Signals and Systems</strong></li>



<li><strong>Circuit Analysis</strong></li>



<li><strong>Communication Systems</strong></li>



<li><strong>Electromagnetic Fields and Waves</strong></li>



<li><strong>Microprocessors and Digital Systems</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.ozyegin.edu.tr/en/electrical-and-electronics-engineering" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here if you want to review the full lesson plan.</a></p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="electrical-electronics-engineering-rankings">Electrical-Electronics Engineering Rankings</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When choosing a university, <strong>success ranking</strong>, scores and scholarship opportunities are decisive for many students. Özyeğin University Electrical-Electronics Engineering department stands out with its academic infrastructure and graduate success, and is in a remarkable position in the rankings.</p>



