<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="differences-between-electrical-engineering-and-electronic-engineering">Differences Between Electrical Engineering and Electronic Engineering</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8220;Electricity or electronics?&#8221; is a common question among students. Although technically under the same roof, the specialization aspects of these two fields are different.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Electrical engineering</strong> deals mostly with large-scale energy systems. This means power generation, transmission and distribution, high voltage systems and motors. Engineers in this field usually work in energy companies, electrical infrastructure projects and automation systems.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Electronics engineering</strong> works at a more micro level. It focuses on areas such as computer hardware, integrated circuits, sensor systems and signal processing. Electronics workers usually work in technology companies, defense industry, mobile device manufacturers or R&amp;D centers.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">At Ozyegin University, these two fields are offered in a blended manner. In other words, while the student has basic knowledge in both fields, he/she has the opportunity to focus on the field of his/her interest in recent years.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-do-electrical-and-electronics-engineering-graduates-do">What Do Electrical and Electronics Engineering Graduates Do?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students graduating from this department take an active role in many sectors in Turkey and around the world. Companies specializing in technology and engineering prioritize graduates from these fields.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="fields-where-graduates-can-work">Fields where graduates can work</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>R&amp;D and Product Development</strong></li>



<li><strong>Software and Hardware Design</strong></li>



<li><strong>Defense Industry</strong> (Aselsan, Roketsan, Havelsan)</li>



<li><strong>Energy and Automation Systems</strong></li>



<li><strong>Communication and Mobile Technologies</strong></li>



<li><strong>Entrepreneurship and Startup Projects</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Especially thanks to the entrepreneurship support offered by Özyeğin University, graduates can become <strong>business building engineers</strong>, not just job seekers.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="senior-project-ideas-for-electrical-and-electronics-engineering">Senior Project Ideas for Electrical and Electronics Engineering</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As a student in this department, I can say that one of the most exciting things is the senior projects. Because you bring together everything you have learned up to that point and turn it into a tangible product. Projects at Özyeğin University are generally chosen to be both technically sound and beneficial to society.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are some creative project ideas:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Wireless energy transfer charger</strong></li>



<li><strong><strong>Autonomous drone system</strong> (for aerial photography or search and rescue)</strong></li>



<li><strong><strong>Intelligent traffic light system</strong> (traffic control with real-time data)</strong></li>



<li><strong><strong>Solar agriculture irrigation system</strong></strong></li>



<li><strong><strong>Sensor-assisted walking stick for the visually impaired</strong></strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some projects can later turn into <strong>startup ideas</strong>. Özyeğin University&#8217;s <a href="https://www.ozyegin.edu.tr/tr/girisimcilik-merkezi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Entrepreneurship Center</a> (Venture Factory) provides mentorship and financial support to such projects. In this way, the project does not remain in the notebook, but comes to life.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="special-entrepreneurship-program-for-international-students-height">Special Entrepreneurship Program for International Students: HEIght</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University not only offers technical knowledge, but also supports its students in entrepreneurship. One of the best examples of this is the <strong>HEIght Program</strong>: &#8220;Higher Education Innovation Growth and Training.&#8221;</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This program is part of a larger EU-funded project in partnership with <strong>EIT Climate-KIC</strong> and universities from different countries. Specifically designed to <strong>increase the participation of international students in the entrepreneurship ecosystem</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="program-features">Program Features</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Participation is free</strong>: Open to all Özyeğin University international students and completely free of charge.</li>



<li><strong>The language of instruction is English</strong> and takes place face-to-face on weekends.</li>



<li><strong>Date</strong>: Saturday and Sunday, May 6 &#8211; 7, 2023</li>



<li><strong>Location</strong>: Ozyegin University Cekmekoy Campus</li>



<li><strong>Scope</strong>: Entrepreneurship workshops, business idea development seminars, mentoring sessions.</li>



<li><strong>Participation requirement</strong>: Attendance is mandatory for all sessions.</li>



<li><strong>Award</strong>: Certificates and financial support for successful projects.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-will-you-learn">What Will You Learn?</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>How to test a business idea </li>



<li>How to get involved in the Turkish entrepreneurship ecosystem</li>



<li>How to communicate with investors </li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">So far, over 100 international students from more than 20 countries have participated in the program and started their entrepreneurial journey.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-apply">How to Apply</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the past, the program was run through an open application form. For new semester announcements, you can get information by sending an e-mail to <strong><a>girişimcilik@ozyegin.edu.tr</a></strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information, you can also fill out the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdEzxwHDVC1OSlyqsw7Fsd0QGRG05DJo3zA0ezkQ7Zx8pEjmQ/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>HEIght Program</strong></a> form.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-do-electrical-and-electronics-engineering-graduates-do">What Do Electrical and Electronics Engineering Graduates Do?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Electrical and Electronics Engineering graduates have a wide range of job opportunities. Özyeğin University is in a very advantageous position in this regard. Thanks to its strong academic staff and the ties it has established with the industry, students start receiving job offers before graduation.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Graduates usually find jobs in the following sectors:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Defense industry</strong> (companies such as ASELSAN, TAI, Roketsan)</li>



<li><strong>Software and technology companies</strong> (ASELSAN, Siemens, Huawei, Arçelik)</li>



<li><strong>Energy companies</strong> (TEİAŞ, Enerjisa)</li>



<li><strong>Automotive electronics and control systems</strong> (Ford Otosan, TOGG)</li>



<li><strong>R&amp;D centers</strong> and graduate programs (both in Turkey and abroad)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are also opportunities for those who want to pursue an academic career in the department. Özyeğin University is looking for new academic staff for <strong>Electrical-Electronics Engineering</strong> as of 2024. This is a great opportunity for graduates who want to do research. </p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process-and-scholarship-opportunities">Application Process and Scholarship Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applying to Ozyegin University as an international student is very practical. Applications are made directly to the university online, and most of the time you do not need to take exams such as YÖS. Especially for graduate programs, students are exempted from the <strong>Graduate Education Entrance Exam</strong>. This makes the application process much easier.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="documents-required-for-application">Documents Required for Application</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>High school diploma and transcript </li>



<li>English proficiency certificate (TOEFL, IELTS or university internal exam)</li>



<li>Copy of passport</li>



<li>Letter of intent and letter of reference, if applicable</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Once you have prepared all your documents, it is enough to upload them to the application system. But don&#8217;t forget, if you are coming to Turkey to study, you need to know about the <strong><a href="http://roadtostudy.com" data-type="link" data-id="roadtostudy.com">Turkey Student Visa application process and required documents</a></strong>. The visa process is the second important stage after university admission.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="elektrik-elektronik-engineering-at-ozyegin">Electrical-Electronics Engineering at Özyeğin</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Electrical-Electronics Engineering is not only a profession, but also a field that shapes technology. Özyeğin University, on the other hand, is one of the rare institutions that enables you to both lay solid theoretical foundations of this field and produce real solutions in practice.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Whether you want to work in the defense industry or develop artificial intelligence-based projects, this department can open doors for you. The academic quality, combined with the global vision and living opportunities that Istanbul offers, make it a really good choice.</p>



