 Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A person receiving financial aid from a support center in Turkiye.","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/","name":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","datePublished":"2026-03-17T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-21T00:57:58+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","keywords":"seasonal support","datePublished":"2026-03-17T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-21T00:57:58+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover seasonal support opportunities in Turkey! Scholarships, one-time grants, and special solutions for international students await you. Find out now!","name":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Financial issues can sometimes be as challenging as education for students studying at university in Turkey. Especially for foreign students, seeking financial support in an unfamiliar system can be a confusing process. However, with the right information, <strong>Turkey&#8217;s seasonal support</strong> opportunities are much wider and more accessible than one might think.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In this article, we will examine in detail the seasonal support and one-time assistance systems and who can benefit from these supports.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 23px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-basis-of-education-supports-who-when-how-can-benefit">The Basis of Education Supports: Who, When, How Can Benefit?</h3>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="purpose-and-scope-of-periodic-support">Purpose and scope of seasonal support</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Seasonal subsidies are scholarship, loan or aid programs that are usually open for application at specific time periods and are repeated annually. These are offered by both public and private institutions. KYK scholarships in particular stand out with applications made at the beginning of the year.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the table below, you can see the types of seasonal support commonly offered in Turkey:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Type of Support</strong></th>
<th><strong>Duration</strong></th>
<th><strong>Application Period</strong></th>
<th><strong>Eligible Applicants</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>KYK Scholarship and Loan</td>
<td>9 months (each academic year)</td>
<td>October – November</td>
<td>Turkish citizens and international students</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Municipal Educational Assistance</td>
<td>One-time / Annual</td>
<td>November – December</td>
<td>Students residing in the municipality</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>NGO and Foundation Scholarships</td>
<td>Varies</td>
<td>Usually Fall Semester</td>
<td>Those who meet the specific application criteria</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-can-apply-for-these-supports">Who can apply for these supports?</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In general, undergraduate, graduate and doctoral students are eligible for support. However, some institutions also include open education or secondary education students. There are also many support programs for international students. For a detailed application guide, you can check our article: <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-burs-danismanligi/" data-type="post" data-id="2993">Scholarship Counseling and Application Support Services in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-times-and-documents-to-be-considered">Application times and documents to be considered</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each type of support has a different application deadline. However, in general, the fall semester is the busiest application period. Documents include a student certificate, transcript, photocopy of ID and proof of income. Applying with incomplete documents can lead to an outright rejection.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="one-time-financial-aid-quick-solution-for-sudden-expenses">One-Time Financial Aid: Quick Solution for Sudden Expenses</h3>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="emergency-aid-from-municipalities-and-governorates">Emergency aid from municipalities and governorates</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most immediate costs students face can be registration fees, dormitory payments or health-related expenses. In these cases, <strong>one-time support</strong> offered by governorships, district governorships or local municipalities comes into play.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="special-support-packages-offered-by-foundations">Special support packages offered by foundations</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some foundations offer special support plans for unforeseen circumstances that may arise for students. For example, separate funds may be set up to cover exam fees or stationery costs. These aids can usually be obtained with a petition and a declaration of need.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="ways-to-get-help-in-necessary-situations">Ways to get help in necessary situations</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can apply to the Social Assistance and Solidarity Foundation in your district for help in times of need. In addition, the scholarship offices of some universities&#8217; student affairs departments can provide referrals for emergency relief funds.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The financial support provided by the TOBB Young Entrepreneurs Board is also very valuable in this sense. This support, which is provided for young people to develop their own projects, contributes to both their education and entrepreneurship careers.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="opportunities-from-kyk-tubitak-and-development-agencies">Opportunities from KYK, TUBITAK and Development Agencies</h3>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="kyk-scholarships-and-student-loans">KYK scholarships and student loans</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KYK is the largest state-funded scholarship and loan network in Turkey. Tens of thousands of students receive support through this system every year. Scholarship and loan applications are made through e-Government. Loan repayments begin after graduation and are interest-free.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-2209-a-and-similar-project-supports">TUBITAK 2209-A and similar project supports</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <a href="https://tubitak.gov.tr/tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TUBITAK&#8217;s </a><strong>2209-A University Students Research Projects Support Program</strong> is a great opportunity for undergraduate students who want to do research. Especially for students who aim for a career in the scientific field, this support makes a great contribution both financially and academically.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more examples of research projects and fellowships, check out <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-az-bilinen-burslar/" data-type="post" data-id="2991">Little-Known But Valuable Fellowship Opportunities in Turkey</a>.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="international-students-term-support-guide">International Students Term Support Guide</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-pay-attention-to-in-the-application-process">What to pay attention to in the application process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Receiving <strong>semester support</strong> in Turkey for international students may require some additional documentation and application steps. The most critical issue is to have a valid residence permit and student document. Many institutions make it clear that support is only available to students legally residing in Turkey.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Common problems students face when applying for support include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Documents not translated into Turkish</li>



<li>Not current residence permit</li>



<li>Missed email notifications</li>



<li>Skipping deadlines</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In Turkey, being systematic and careful when applying for seasonal support</strong> is often a prerequisite for acceptance.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="documents-related-to-visa-status-and-residence-permit">Documents related to visa status and residence permit</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most frequently asked documents when applying for scholarships and other support include visa type and residence documents. Students must submit these documents in full and clearly document their status of stay in Turkey.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some types of support are only available to students arriving on a study visa. It is therefore necessary to read the terms and conditions of the support provider carefully before applying.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="language-proficiency-or-other-special-conditions">Language proficiency or other special conditions</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some special scholarship programs may require Turkish proficiency or a certain level of academic achievement. For example, TUBITAK scholarships require academic qualifications such as project writing. It is therefore important to check the criteria required by the support provider before applying, such as language level or GPA.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is also possible for students to combine sponsorships from their home countries with support in Turkey by adapting them to the Turkish system. At this point, it is very useful to be in contact with the international student office of the university.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="now-is-the-time-to-apply-step-up-before-its-too-late">Now is the Time to Apply: Step Up Before It&#8217;s Too Late!</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For every student in Turkey, financial support is not only a source of funding, but also an investment in the future. Dozens of scholarships and aid options, both public and private, are here to support your academic and personal development.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>You can chart your own path by applying for seasonal support</strong> in Turkey in a timely manner. Remember, sometimes the most valuable support is the least known.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you need more information about support, the <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a> team is ready to guide you through the application process. By getting counseling, you can minimize the risk of making mistakes and access the right support in the fastest way.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Now you know: No plan becomes reality without action.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-03-17T07:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-20T21:57:58Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp","alt":"A person receiving financial aid from a support center in Turkiye.","title":"periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'seasonal-support-in-turkey';
UPDATE "revisions" SET "data" = json_set("data", '$.source_seo', json('{"title":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","description":"Discover seasonal support opportunities in Turkey! Scholarships, one-time grants, and special solutions for international students await you. Find out now!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","ogDescription":"Discover seasonal support opportunities in Turkey! Scholarships, one-time grants, and special solutions for international students await you. Find out now!","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1-1024x772.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","twitterDescription":"Discover seasonal support opportunities in Turkey! Scholarships, one-time grants, and special solutions for international students await you. Find out now!","canonicalPath":"/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-donemsel-destek/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A person receiving financial aid from a support center in Turkiye.","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/","name":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","datePublished":"2026-03-17T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-21T00:57:58+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","keywords":"seasonal support","datePublished":"2026-03-17T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-21T00:57:58+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover seasonal support opportunities in Turkey! Scholarships, one-time grants, and special solutions for international students await you. Find out now!","name":"Seasonal Support in Türkiye 2025: 5 Unknown Opportunities","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/seasonal-support-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Financial issues can sometimes be as challenging as education for students studying at university in Turkey. Especially for foreign students, seeking financial support in an unfamiliar system can be a confusing process. However, with the right information, <strong>Turkey&#8217;s seasonal support</strong> opportunities are much wider and more accessible than one might think.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In this article, we will examine in detail the seasonal support and one-time assistance systems and who can benefit from these supports.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 23px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-basis-of-education-supports-who-when-how-can-benefit">The Basis of Education Supports: Who, When, How Can Benefit?</h3>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="purpose-and-scope-of-periodic-support">Purpose and scope of seasonal support</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Seasonal subsidies are scholarship, loan or aid programs that are usually open for application at specific time periods and are repeated annually. These are offered by both public and private institutions. KYK scholarships in particular stand out with applications made at the beginning of the year.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the table below, you can see the types of seasonal support commonly offered in Turkey:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Type of Support</strong></th>
<th><strong>Duration</strong></th>
<th><strong>Application Period</strong></th>
<th><strong>Eligible Applicants</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>KYK Scholarship and Loan</td>
<td>9 months (each academic year)</td>
<td>October – November</td>
<td>Turkish citizens and international students</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Municipal Educational Assistance</td>
<td>One-time / Annual</td>
<td>November – December</td>
<td>Students residing in the municipality</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>NGO and Foundation Scholarships</td>
<td>Varies</td>
<td>Usually Fall Semester</td>
<td>Those who meet the specific application criteria</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-can-apply-for-these-supports">Who can apply for these supports?</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In general, undergraduate, graduate and doctoral students are eligible for support. However, some institutions also include open education or secondary education students. There are also many support programs for international students. For a detailed application guide, you can check our article: <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-burs-danismanligi/" data-type="post" data-id="2993">Scholarship Counseling and Application Support Services in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-times-and-documents-to-be-considered">Application times and documents to be considered</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each type of support has a different application deadline. However, in general, the fall semester is the busiest application period. Documents include a student certificate, transcript, photocopy of ID and proof of income. Applying with incomplete documents can lead to an outright rejection.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="one-time-financial-aid-quick-solution-for-sudden-expenses">One-Time Financial Aid: Quick Solution for Sudden Expenses</h3>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="emergency-aid-from-municipalities-and-governorates">Emergency aid from municipalities and governorates</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most immediate costs students face can be registration fees, dormitory payments or health-related expenses. In these cases, <strong>one-time support</strong> offered by governorships, district governorships or local municipalities comes into play.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="special-support-packages-offered-by-foundations">Special support packages offered by foundations</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some foundations offer special support plans for unforeseen circumstances that may arise for students. For example, separate funds may be set up to cover exam fees or stationery costs. These aids can usually be obtained with a petition and a declaration of need.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="ways-to-get-help-in-necessary-situations">Ways to get help in necessary situations</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can apply to the Social Assistance and Solidarity Foundation in your district for help in times of need. In addition, the scholarship offices of some universities&#8217; student affairs departments can provide referrals for emergency relief funds.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The financial support provided by the TOBB Young Entrepreneurs Board is also very valuable in this sense. This support, which is provided for young people to develop their own projects, contributes to both their education and entrepreneurship careers.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="opportunities-from-kyk-tubitak-and-development-agencies">Opportunities from KYK, TUBITAK and Development Agencies</h3>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="kyk-scholarships-and-student-loans">KYK scholarships and student loans</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KYK is the largest state-funded scholarship and loan network in Turkey. Tens of thousands of students receive support through this system every year. Scholarship and loan applications are made through e-Government. Loan repayments begin after graduation and are interest-free.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-2209-a-and-similar-project-supports">TUBITAK 2209-A and similar project supports</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <a href="https://tubitak.gov.tr/tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TUBITAK&#8217;s </a><strong>2209-A University Students Research Projects Support Program</strong> is a great opportunity for undergraduate students who want to do research. Especially for students who aim for a career in the scientific field, this support makes a great contribution both financially and academically.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more examples of research projects and fellowships, check out <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-az-bilinen-burslar/" data-type="post" data-id="2991">Little-Known But Valuable Fellowship Opportunities in Turkey</a>.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="international-students-term-support-guide">International Students Term Support Guide</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-pay-attention-to-in-the-application-process">What to pay attention to in the application process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Receiving <strong>semester support</strong> in Turkey for international students may require some additional documentation and application steps. The most critical issue is to have a valid residence permit and student document. Many institutions make it clear that support is only available to students legally residing in Turkey.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Common problems students face when applying for support include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Documents not translated into Turkish</li>



<li>Not current residence permit</li>



<li>Missed email notifications</li>



<li>Skipping deadlines</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In Turkey, being systematic and careful when applying for seasonal support</strong> is often a prerequisite for acceptance.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="documents-related-to-visa-status-and-residence-permit">Documents related to visa status and residence permit</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most frequently asked documents when applying for scholarships and other support include visa type and residence documents. Students must submit these documents in full and clearly document their status of stay in Turkey.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some types of support are only available to students arriving on a study visa. It is therefore necessary to read the terms and conditions of the support provider carefully before applying.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="language-proficiency-or-other-special-conditions">Language proficiency or other special conditions</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some special scholarship programs may require Turkish proficiency or a certain level of academic achievement. For example, TUBITAK scholarships require academic qualifications such as project writing. It is therefore important to check the criteria required by the support provider before applying, such as language level or GPA.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is also possible for students to combine sponsorships from their home countries with support in Turkey by adapting them to the Turkish system. At this point, it is very useful to be in contact with the international student office of the university.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="now-is-the-time-to-apply-step-up-before-its-too-late">Now is the Time to Apply: Step Up Before It&#8217;s Too Late!</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For every student in Turkey, financial support is not only a source of funding, but also an investment in the future. Dozens of scholarships and aid options, both public and private, are here to support your academic and personal development.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>You can chart your own path by applying for seasonal support</strong> in Turkey in a timely manner. Remember, sometimes the most valuable support is the least known.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you need more information about support, the <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a> team is ready to guide you through the application process. By getting counseling, you can minimize the risk of making mistakes and access the right support in the fastest way.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Now you know: No plan becomes reality without action.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-03-17T07:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-20T21:57:58Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye-1.webp","alt":"A person receiving financial aid from a support center in Turkiye.","title":"periodic-and-one-time-support-provided-in-turkiye"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'seasonal-support-in-turkey' );
